==Finnish==

===Etymology===

First participe active (''[[-pä]]'') of negative verb ''[[ei]]''.

===Prefix===
'''epä-'''

#Used to invert the meaning of a word. English counterparts include [[in-]], [[non-]], [[un-]].
#:''[[selvä]]'' (clear) – ''[[epäselvä]]'' (unclear)

====Derived terms====
*most words starting with ''epä-'':
*[[epäaito]]
*[[epäluulo]]
*[[epätoivo]]
*[[epätosi]]
*[[epäuskottava]]

